# ClawChat Server — Environment Variables
# See README.md for details on each connection mode.

# ── Gateway connection ──
# All bots are registered by users via the UI, each with its own gateway config.
# No server-level gateway env vars are needed.

# ── Multi-bot config (optional) ──
# You can pre-configure system bots via env or file, but it's not required.
# Option 1: JSON array in env var (single line)
# BOTS_CONFIG='[{"id":"bot-clawchat","username":"ClawBot","gateway":{"authToken":"token1"},"trigger":"all"}]'
#
# Option 2: Create packages/server/data/bots.json (see README)
#
# If neither is set, no system bots are created — users register bots via the UI.

# ── Auth ──
# Secret key for signing JWT tokens. If not set, a random key is generated
# on each restart (all existing tokens will be invalidated on restart).
# JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-here

# ── Server config ──
PORT=3001
HOST=0.0.0.0

# Public URL for this server (used to build full URLs for remote bots)
# Set this to your Tailscale or externally reachable address
# PUBLIC_URL=http://<tailscale-ip>:3003

# CORS origin for Socket.IO (default: * = allow all)
# Set to a specific origin in production for security:
# CORS_ORIGIN=https://your-frontend.com
# CORS_ORIGIN=*

# Azure Speech Service (STT + TTS)
AZURE_SPEECH_KEY=your-azure-speech-key
AZURE_SPEECH_REGION=centralindia
